user summary:
I love an 'about me' section because how much can you really learn about me only through my titles? 

Where am I from?
Mumbai, India. Often referred to as the city that never sleeps. I, however, get my eight hours every night. 

My journey in a nutshell? 

I've always been a class topper in school and college. I never enjoyed physics, and arts was not considered an option if you got good grades at that time, and so I 'chose' commerce. Once that decision was made, the only option in front of me with my grades was Chartered Accountancy. I cleared all the papers I sat for but luckily realised early on that it wasnt the career for me. So, I walked off. No regrets. Met some of my closest friends through that journey and earned some accounting and tax knowledge that comes in handy today. 

As a result, I started working full time at 19, alongside my studies. I graduated among the top 10 in Mumbai University while working in a Public Relations start up for 2.5 years on projects such as A R Rahman, Swedish House Mafia and many more that were a teenager's dream. Once I left, I worked with a social media firm for a few months and was soon leading their most important projects. Even after being offered early promotions, I didn't think it was the right next step for me. The decision to study further stemmed from there and I pursued and ranked among the top 3 in my Masters in International Business program in Singapore. 

The global exposure broadened my horizons and I wanted more. I worked very hard to find myself a job in France and Sociabble happened. After a good performance selling to the European market, I felt the itch to take this to my own home. I built a case and was permitted to start Sociabble's first Asia office to service this side of the world. Back then it was just me and my laptop and it feels surreal to see the clientele and team we've now built here today. 

While building Sociabble, I also continued to build myself as a multi-passionate professional. I wrote - on social, short stories and now a novel; I advocated for women at work in India; I studied to become a coach and launched my business.

So what do I do today? 

I am the Director of Sociabble, Asia. As pioneers in employee advocacy and employee communication, I have grown to know this industry inside-out. 

I am an ICF certified career and life coach with the goal to help as many people as I can experience the same benefits I have by chasing their dreams - Butterfly Effect Coaching.

At the purest level, I am a writer and now a creator and author. 

And lastly, a forever student.
